A1: (for v,u being (Element of V) holds ((v in W & u in W) implies ( v * u ) in W))
proof
let v being (Element of V),u being (Element of V);
assume that
A2: v in W
and
A3: u in W;
consider u1 being (Function of X,( REAL )) such that A4: u1 = u and A5: ( u1 | X ) is  bounded by A3;
reconsider h = ( v * u ) as (Element of ( Funcs (X,( REAL )) ));
consider v1 being (Function of X,( REAL )) such that A6: v1 = v and A7: ( v1 | X ) is  bounded by A2;
( dom ( v1 (#) u1 ) ) = ( X /\ X ) by FUNCT_2:def 1;
then A8: ( ( v1 (#) u1 ) | X ) is  bounded by A7,A5,RFUNCT_1:84;
( ( dom v1 ) /\ ( dom u1 ) ) = ( X /\ ( dom u1 ) ) by FUNCT_2:def 1;
then A9: ((ex f being Function st ((h = f & ( dom f ) = X) & ( rng f ) c= ( REAL ))) & ( ( dom v1 ) /\ ( dom u1 ) ) = ( X /\ X )) by FUNCT_2:def 1,FUNCT_2:def 2;
(for x being set holds (x in ( dom h ) implies ( h . x ) = ( ( v1 . x ) * ( u1 . x ) ))) by A6,A4,FUNCSDOM:2;
then ( v * u ) = ( v1 (#) u1 ) by A9,VALUED_1:def 4;
hence thesis by A8;
end;
